abstract: >
  Representation Economy is a conceptual framework for understanding
  how artificial intelligence systems, enterprises, institutions,
  markets, and governance systems increasingly operate through
  machine-legible representations of reality.
  
  The repository introduces the SENSE–CORE–DRIVER framework,
  a layered architecture for understanding how AI systems
  perceive reality, reason over institutional context,
  and execute actions within governed legitimacy boundaries.
  
  The framework explores representation infrastructure,
  institutional intelligence, delegated autonomy,
  governed execution, machine-legible reality,
  enterprise AI governance, and representation integrity
  as foundational components of the AI economy.

